story.text: Wow. Yesterday was amazing. I had a 2yr old whitetail buck come directly up to me and start sniffing me. No food on my part. Then we just hung out for 2 hours until he calmly walked away. He seemed to really love the fresh greenery that surrounds the house. I like to think I am not bad company either. He let me scratch his budding horns, covered in velvet as they were.
Looking forward to seeing him again. Feeling so blessed - like I was touched by god.
